<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Deploying WordPress and MySQL with Persistent Volumes with Meshery on Layer5 Academy</title><link>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/</link><description>Recent content in Deploying WordPress and MySQL with Persistent Volumes with Meshery on Layer5 Academy</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Deploying WordPress and MySQL with Persistent Volumes with Meshery</title><link>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p>In this tutorial, you will learn how to deploy a &lt;strong>WordPress site and a MySQL database with Persistent Volumes&lt;/strong> using Meshery Playground. Meshery Playground is an interactive and collaborative live cluster environment that simplifies the deployment process and enhances user experience by providing visual tools for managing Kubernetes resources.&lt;/p>
