&lt;p>&lt;em>Figure: Choose deployment Environment&lt;/em>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Visualize Deployed Resources</title><link>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/visualize/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/visualize/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="visualizing-the-deployed-resources" class="heading-link">
 &lt;strong>Visualizing the Deployed Resources&lt;/strong>
 &lt;a href="#visualizing-the-deployed-resources" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink to this heading">ðŸ”—&lt;/a>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>To view the resources deployed, use the Visualize section of the &lt;em>Kanvas&lt;/em>. In this section, you can apply filters to display the specific resources you want to see.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Move to the Visualize tab.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Click the filter icon and choose the appropriate filters:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>For &amp;ldquo;Kinds&amp;rdquo; select &lt;code>Deployment&lt;/code>, &lt;code>Service&lt;/code>, &lt;code>PersistentVolume&lt;/code>, &lt;code>PersistentVolumeClaim&lt;/code> and &lt;code>Secret&lt;/code>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>For the &amp;ldquo;label&amp;rdquo; select &lt;code>dev=tutorial&lt;/code>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>You can also use the icons on the right sidebar to filter the resources.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Conclusion</title><link>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/conclusion/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud.layer5.io/academy/learning-paths/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/mastering-kubernetes-for-engineers/deploying-wordpress-and-mysql-with-persistent-volumes-with-meshery/sql/conclusion/</guid><description>&lt;p>Congratulations! Youâ€™ve successfully completed the tutorial on deploying a WordPress site and MySQL database with Persistent Volumes using Meshery Playground. This hands-on experience should have given you valuable insights into importing manifest files, visualizing resources, creating persistent volumes, and managing deployments in Meshery Playground.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>